text: <@U3B9R5C58> - in the v0.6 architecture, chaincode serially processed per transaction per block / batch (i.e. a batches are processed serially in order and transactions within each batch are also processed serially and committed together).    In the new architecture, this is also currently the case although we will be moving to a model where transactions submitted to different "chains / channels" can be executed concurrently
